<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id600b56d9-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58" identifier="/us/usc/t30/s708"><num value="708">§ 708.</num><heading> Assignments; succession</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Rights and privileges to qualify as an applicant under this chapter shall not be assignable, but may pass through devise or descent.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id600b56da-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58">(<ref href="/us/pl/87/851/s8">Pub. L. 87–851, § 8</ref>, <date date="1962-10-23">Oct. 23, 1962</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/76/1128">76 Stat. 1128</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
